11.6.23  4:52 pm   I recently showed someone a non-musical project of mine, and they said "I can't wait to see what you do with that next," and now I can't work on it at all. It was like magic. Because of this,  I've come to a hypothesis that my a lot of my recent creative block with music is caused by thinking about what other people will think about my music, because my block started around the time I started showing other people my music. Does that sound like a plausible hypothesis?

     yes

      If so, what do I do about it? Do I have to make a pact with myself to never show anyone my music ever? To be fair, I'd rather "make music by myself and not show it to anyone" than "be afraid to make music at all".

     the curse is not necessarily that other people heard it, the curse came from the fact that you participated in their listening -- you showed it to them personally, and you heard their reaction personally. this can be avoided by instead posting it somewhere where people CAN find it, but you don't know exactly who and when
